About this property

Located in Kaş, this villa is in the mountains and on the waterfront. The area's natural beauty can be seen at Kaputas Beach and Patara Beach. Discover the area's water adventures with jet skiing and kayaking nearby, or enjoy the great outdoors with hiking/biking trails and cycling.
Villa Amycha

Contemporary villa – sleeps 8 +1 in 5 bedrooms. Daily maid service, Heated Infinity Pool with Jacuzzi jet seating, Outdoor Bar, BBQ and fabulous Sea Views ideal for entertaining and relaxing. Located in the upmarket and unspoilt resort of Kalkan, on Turkey's gorgeous Turquoise Coast, Villa Amycha is fully equipped for a fantastic family or friends holiday.

Included in the Rental rates -
* Complimentary Pool Heating (28 degrees)
* Daily Maid Service
* Complimentary Wifi
* Air-conditioning throughout
* Complimentary bathroom amenities on arrival
* A food and drink welcome pack on arrival
* Complimentary starter pack of Nespresso Coffee capsules for Coffee Machine
* Daily fresh bread delivery
* Complimentary Bottled Water in the water chiller
* Daily Pool/Garden Service
* Complimentary Villa Phone for calls to local restaurants/businesses/Turkish mobiles
* Breakfast prepared, served cleared away daily (subject to you having provisions in the kitchen)
* Bathroom Towels, Pool Towels Beach Towels for use during your stay
* Linen and Bathroom Towels changed on day 7 of a 2 week stay
* Pre-arranging airport transfers, car hire, grocery deliveries, or help with booking chefs or babysitters.
* Our villa manager to assist should any emergencies arise during your stay

The huge south facing Pool Terrace with views over both Kalkan and Kalamar Bays is the perfect spot for sunbathing, swimming, relaxing in the jacuzzi, dining, sipping a cocktail at the bar or enjoying sundowners whilst appreciating the amazing views from the shaded lounge area. Equipped with 8 comfortable Sun Loungers with parasols, external Dining Table seating up to 10, contemporary sofa seating, a marble wet bar with bar stools and of course the requisite barbecue for those occasional nights when you're not tempted by the delights of Kalkan's renowned restaurants!

In addition you can escape the sun and get a little more active in the shaded area playing Table Tennis, Air Hockey or Pool or perhaps backgammon or chess at the games table: Ideal for children and teens!

Inside, Villa Amycha is just as impressive; - with 220m2 of built area it is spacious and airy and has fabulous views from all rooms. The open plan lounge, dining room and kitchen is fully equipped and tastefully and comfortably furnished in a contemporary style. There is WiFi throughout, Apple TV and full DigiTurk digital channel provision giving a vast array of English language Movies, News, Sports Children's channels on all 3 TVs in the property.

There are 3 Ensuite Double Bedrooms, an Ensuite Twin Bedroom and a Single Bedroom. All bedrooms are air-conditioned, all have hairdryers, and all, except the single room, have private balconies or terrace with amazing views over the pool, Kalkan and both Kalkan and Kalamar Bays. Both the Master bedroom and the second Guest Bedroom have flatscreen TVs.

There is a fully equipped kitchen laundry room for your personal use, but a stay at Villa Amycha is guaranteed to be relaxing as daily maid service, the services of a gardener/pool man and fresh bread delivery every morning is included: A truly luxurious and relaxing break in scenic surroundings in a fabulous location!!

IMPORTANT NOTE
Due to a number of stone steps the villa is not suitable for those with mobility issues. Parents please be aware that although we do have a stair-gate on the external staircase leading to the pool terrace, there are no stair-gates inside the villa.
Very young babies are welcome and a travel cot and high chair can be provided. Children of any age must be supervised by a responsible adult at all times.

No floatation devices such as lilos, inflatable boats or similar to be used in the pool by children without responsible adult supervision due to the potential to float over the sheer edge of the infinity pool.
